org.apache.felix.ipojo.dependency.impl

Class ServiceReferenceManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.felix.ipojo.dependency.impl.ServiceReferenceManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TrackerCustomizer

    public class ServiceReferenceManager
extends Object
implements TrackerCustomizer
    This class is handling the transformations between the base service set and the selected service set. It handles the matching services and the selected service set. As this class is tied to the dependency model, it reuses the same locks objects.

      • addingService

        public boolean addingService(ServiceReference reference)
        Description copied from interface: TrackerCustomizer
        A service is being added to the Tracker object. This method is called before a service which matched the search parameters of the Tracker object is added to it. This method should return the service object to be tracked for this ServiceReference object. If this method returns true, the service object becomes available from the Tracker.getService() and Tracker.getServices() methods. However notice that the service is still not accessible at that time.
        Specified by:
        addingService in interface TrackerCustomizer
        Parameters:
        reference - the Reference to service being added to the Tracker object.
        Returns:
        true if the service reference must be tracked. false ff the service reference must be ignored (un-tracked)

      • addedService

        public void addedService(ServiceReference reference)
        Description copied from interface: TrackerCustomizer
        A service tracked by the Tracker object has been added in the list. This method is called when a service has been added in the managed list (after addingService) and if the service has not disappeared before during the callback. In this method, the service object is accessible from the Tracker.getService() and Tracker.getServices() method.
        Specified by:
        addedService in interface TrackerCustomizer
        Parameters:
        reference - the added reference.

      • getTrackingInterceptorReferences

        public List<ServiceReference> getTrackingInterceptorReferences()
        Gets the list of tracking interceptors attached to the current service dependency.
        Returns:
        the list of service references of the tracking interceptors participating to the resolution of the current service dependency. An empty list is returned is there are no participating interceptors.
        Since:
        1.11.0

      • getBindingInterceptorReferences

        Since:
        1.11.0

      • getRankingInterceptorReference

        public ServiceReference getRankingInterceptorReference()
        Gets the service reference of the currently attached ranking interceptor. As only one ranking interceptor can be attached at a point on time, this is not a list but only one reference.
        Returns:
        the service reference of the ranking interceptor participating to the resolution of the current service dependency. null if no (external) ranking interceptor is currently attached.
        Since:
        1.11.0
